ions; dependency audit\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q7: Existing libraries?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Q7: diff+mammoth+cheerio+remark+pdf-parse all BSD/MIT, actively maintained\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-13T15:55:00Z\",\"durationMs\":60000}\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":8,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Validation corpus and acceptance metrics\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.78,\"noveltyJustification\":\"First quantification of acceptance criteria with specific numerical targets and ~33 fixture pairs\",\"keyQuestions\":[],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-13T16:00:00Z\",\"durationMs\":60000}\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":9,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Architecture synthesis\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.55,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Consolidated architecture diagram, technology stack table, phase map are new synthesized artifacts\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q1: Canonical representation?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Q1: Structured token model with sections[], fidelity scoring, format-specific adapters\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-13T16:05:00Z\",\"durationMs\":60000}\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":10,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Gap analysis and remaining open questions\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.40,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Systematic gap analysis, edge-case handling table, all 7 primary questions now answered with evidence\",\"keyQuestions\":[],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-13T16:10:00Z\",\"durationMs\":60000}\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"totalIterations\":10,\"answeredCount\":7,\"totalQuestions\":7,\"stopReason\":\"maxIterationsReached\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-13T16:15:00Z\"}"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/136-standalone-document-diff-skill/001-research-and-requirements/research/lineages/document-diff-3/deep-research-state.jsonl\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/136-standalone-document-diff-skill/001-research-and-requirements/research/lineages/document-diff-3/deep-research-state.jsonl\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/136-standalone-document-diff-skill/001-research-and-requirements/research/lineages/document-diff-3/deep-research-state.jsonl\n@@ -1,4 +1,12 @@\n {\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Research the architecture and v1 contract for the standalone local AI document diff skill\",\"maxIterations\":10,\"convergenceThreshold\":0,\"stuckThreshold\":3,\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/136-standalone-document-diff-skill/001-research-and-requirements\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-13T15:00:00Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-document-diff-3-1783944168326-lgic9n\",\"stopPolicy\":\"max-iterations\"}\n {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":1,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Canonical representations and format adapters survey\",\"findingsCount\":6,\"newInfoRatio\":1.0,\"noveltyJustification\":\"First pass; all findings are new to this packet\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q1: Which canonical representation and adapters?\",\"Q6: Format support matrix?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Character-only diff as primary approach\",\"reason\":\"Loses document structure; structural tokenization is required\",\"evidence\":\"iteration-001.md\"}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-13T15:15:00Z\",\"durationMs\":180000}\n {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":2,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Diff algorithms and format adapter libraries deep dive\",\"findingsCount\":6,\"newInfoRatio\":0.9,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Confirmed jsdiff extensibility from iter-1 and identified concrete libraries (mammoth, cheerio, remark) with exact APIs for each format tier\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q2: Which diff algorithms?\",\"Q7: Which existing libraries?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Q2: Myers via jsdiff for v1 core, histogram as upgrade path\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Custom markdown parser instead of remark/mdast\",\"reason\":\"remark/mdast is the established ecosystem standard with plugin support\",\"evidence\":\"iteration-002.md\"},{\"approach\":\"jsdom for HTML extraction\",\"reason\":\"cheerio is lighter, faster, and sufficient for structural extraction\",\"evidence\":\"iteration-002.md\"}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-13T15:25:00Z\",\"durationMs\":180000}\n {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":3,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Snapshot lifecycle design\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.85,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Designed complete snapshot state machine with content-addressed storage, retention policy, atomicity, security, and concurrency\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q3: Which snapshot lifecycle is safe and predictable?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Q3: Content-addressed SHA-256 snapshots with 30-day LRU retention, atomic writes, explicit-pair fallback\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"SQLite for snapshot metadata\",\"reason\":\"Overkill for v1; flat file index is simpler and more portable\",\"evidence\":\"iteration-003.md\"},{\"approach\":\"In-memory snapshot cache\",\"reason\":\"Loses data on crash; disk-first with atomic writes is safer\",\"evidence\":\"iteration-003.md\"}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-13T15:35:00Z\",\"durationMs\":120000}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":4,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"HTML report design\",\"findingsCount\":6,\"newInfoRatio\":0.82,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Concrete visual encoding, CSP specification, fidelity dashboard, keyboard navigation model\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q4: How should the HTML report expose fidelity and risk?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Q4: Self-contained dual-mode HTML with CSP script-src none, fidelity dashboard, keyboard nav\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-13T15